WEBVTT

00:01.468 --> 00:03.469
- [car horn honks]
- ♪ School is out ♪

00:03.536 --> 00:04.571
♪ The day is done ♪

00:04.637 --> 00:06.272
♪ But for you
it's just begun ♪

00:06.339 --> 00:07.574
♪ Welcome home ♪

00:07.640 --> 00:10.510
♪ Welcome to The Wayne ♪
- ♪ I'm so glad you came ♪

00:10.577 --> 00:12.679
- ♪ Around every corner ♪

00:12.746 --> 00:15.415
♪ Behind every door ♪

00:15.482 --> 00:17.784
♪ Adventure is waiting ♪

00:17.851 --> 00:20.920
♪ So no hesitating ♪

00:20.987 --> 00:23.189
- ♪ Explore ♪
- ♪ What you can't explain ♪

00:23.256 --> 00:25.859
{\an5}- ♪ Explore ♪
- ♪ Welcome to the Wayne ♪

00:25.925 --> 00:28.495
- ♪ Explore ♪
- ♪ Welcome to the Wayne ♪♪

00:31.531 --> 00:33.800
{\an8}- [dog barking]
- [car horn honking]

00:33.867 --> 00:35.835
{\an8}- I don't know
about this, Olly.

00:35.902 --> 00:37.337
{\an8}- Getting rid of
your old stuff?

00:37.404 --> 00:39.272
{\an8}That's what makes
flea markets so much fun.

00:39.339 --> 00:41.441
{\an8}That and the fleas.
[scratching]

00:41.508 --> 00:43.376
{\an8}- I notice you're not
getting rid of anything.

00:43.443 --> 00:45.245
{\an8}- Everything
I own sparks joy.

00:45.311 --> 00:46.646
{\an8}Besides, I'm more
of a buy guy.

00:46.713 --> 00:48.581
{\an8}- [fluttering money]
- [elevator bell dings]

00:48.648 --> 00:50.150
{\an8}- Hey, Olly, Ansi!

00:50.216 --> 00:53.153
{\an8}Welcome to The Wayne
Swap Shop, Hop &amp; Bop.

00:53.219 --> 00:54.921
- We can trade stuff,
buy stuff--

00:54.988 --> 00:56.556
- And then shake
your dorsal fins

00:56.623 --> 00:59.459
in our under-the-sea
themed dance party.

00:59.526 --> 01:00.460
[chuckles]

01:00.527 --> 01:02.562
- I think this year's
disco beat.

01:02.629 --> 01:05.565
{\an8}- Then why am I wearing
these flippers?

01:05.632 --> 01:09.169
{\an8}Oh, sure, walk away
when I need you two the most.

01:09.235 --> 01:11.704
{\an8}I am not changing.
- [flippers flapping]

01:11.771 --> 01:15.408
- CROWD:
[mixed conversations]

01:16.443 --> 01:19.045
- Wow, look at all this
hot swapping action.

01:19.112 --> 01:21.047
- I'm only here because
my dad's making me.

01:21.114 --> 01:22.715
He says there's
not enough room

01:22.782 --> 01:24.217
in our apartment
for all of this.

01:24.284 --> 01:26.152
- Ansi, sometimes you've
gotta let go of old stuff,

01:26.219 --> 01:28.321
to make way for the new,
or gently used.

01:28.388 --> 01:31.157
- ANDREI: [sighs]
- Andrei, snap out of it!

01:31.224 --> 01:34.394
If you wanna sell anything,
you need to smile.

01:34.461 --> 01:36.062
[gasps]

01:36.129 --> 01:38.398
- How can I smile
when I just found out

01:38.465 --> 01:40.300
that I'm the last
of my kind.

01:40.366 --> 01:42.235
I'll never meet
another vampire.

01:42.302 --> 01:44.270
- Then you've gotta
hang on to this stuff.

01:44.337 --> 01:46.272
It's all you've got
left of your past.

01:46.339 --> 01:48.241
It's like part of
who you are.

01:48.308 --> 01:51.411
- Yeah, and this is actually
part of who you are.

01:51.478 --> 01:53.613
- Thanks, I was
looking for that.

01:53.680 --> 01:54.914
But the rest can go.

01:54.981 --> 01:57.050
What am I hanging
on to, anyway?

01:57.116 --> 01:59.052
A bunch of old '70s clothes,

01:59.118 --> 02:00.487
a harpoon,

02:00.553 --> 02:02.222
this sharp pillow.

02:02.288 --> 02:04.324
- This stuff is all great!

02:04.390 --> 02:06.192
My only problem is I don't
know what to collect.

02:06.259 --> 02:07.527
- That's not
your only problem.

02:07.594 --> 02:09.795
- Every year, I try to
start a collection.

02:09.863 --> 02:11.097
But nothing seems to stick.

02:11.164 --> 02:12.565
- [gum pops]
- This was on your butt.

02:12.632 --> 02:14.767
- Except for old sticky,
the butt gum.

02:14.834 --> 02:16.302
[chomps]
- ANSI: [gags]

02:16.369 --> 02:18.204
- As much as I'd like
to hear the rest

02:18.271 --> 02:19.939
of this scintillating
conversation,

02:20.006 --> 02:21.708
I've got
bargaining to do.

02:21.774 --> 02:24.143
- Uh-oh, here she goes.

02:24.210 --> 02:27.747
- Wherever there's an
overpriced box of doorknobs,

02:27.814 --> 02:29.349
you'll find her.
- Find who?

02:29.415 --> 02:31.551
- Wherever there's
a two-for-one deal,

02:31.618 --> 02:34.454
she'll get you three--
for free!

02:34.521 --> 02:35.622
- Doorknobs?

02:35.688 --> 02:37.624
- Savior of the sale,
defender of the deal,

02:37.690 --> 02:39.058
master of merch.

02:39.125 --> 02:40.827
- Is she come kind
of magical wizard?

02:40.894 --> 02:45.632
- No, she's...the Pack Rat.

02:45.698 --> 02:46.833
- ♪ She's the Pack Rat ♪

02:46.900 --> 02:48.902
- Nice hat.
- You wanted $20?

02:48.968 --> 02:50.236
Make that $5.

02:50.303 --> 02:52.672
- Pffft. Half off.
Big deal.

02:52.739 --> 02:55.642
- ♪ She's the Pack Rat ♪

02:55.708 --> 03:01.047
♪ Collectin' stuff
is where it's at ♪

03:01.114 --> 03:04.284
♪ She's the Pack Rat ♪

03:05.585 --> 03:07.520
♪ Oh yeah ♪

03:07.587 --> 03:09.355
♪ Uh-huh ♪

03:09.422 --> 03:11.824
♪ She's the Pack Rat ♪

03:11.891 --> 03:13.026
- Interesting selection...

03:13.092 --> 03:14.594
of useless garbage.

03:14.661 --> 03:17.730
- Oh, you are
the famous Pack Rat.

03:17.797 --> 03:20.867
You're supposed to pull the wool
over my eyes and clean me out.

03:20.934 --> 03:23.002
- Maybe.
- Or maybe not.

03:23.069 --> 03:25.738
Because perhaps I think
you've finally met your match.

03:25.805 --> 03:29.208
I'm sure I have something
you cannot live without.

03:29.275 --> 03:30.543
- Doubt it.

03:30.610 --> 03:32.245
- For every buyer,
there exists an item

03:32.312 --> 03:34.914
that is the perfect fit.

03:34.981 --> 03:36.182
Like a lock...

03:36.249 --> 03:37.784
und a key.

03:37.850 --> 03:38.918
[grunting]
Oh, yes.

03:38.985 --> 03:39.919
[grunting]

03:39.986 --> 03:41.721
Get in, stupid key!

03:41.788 --> 03:44.490
Key of my nightmares!

03:44.557 --> 03:47.794
Ah, that didn't work out,
but you get the idea.

03:47.860 --> 03:49.028
- What's in the box?

03:49.095 --> 03:50.330
- The box?

03:50.396 --> 03:53.600
Oh, so the Pack Rat
likes some mystery.

03:53.666 --> 03:55.602
- No, but I'll give
you $5 for it.

03:55.668 --> 03:57.870
- How could you put
a price on the unknown?

03:57.937 --> 03:59.172
- All right, $10.

03:59.238 --> 04:01.040
- The thrill of discovery.

04:01.107 --> 04:02.475
- $11.

04:02.542 --> 04:05.044
- The rush of finding a hidden
treasure inside of a box--

04:05.111 --> 04:07.547
like those storage shows.
- $13!

04:07.614 --> 04:11.684
- On the airplane TV!
- This is everything I've got!

04:11.751 --> 04:14.287
- You talked me into
it, Pack Rat.

04:14.354 --> 04:17.055
I hope you've found
your perfect fit.

04:17.123 --> 04:18.524
- [box clicks]
- What?

04:18.591 --> 04:20.726
You tricked me.
This is junk.

04:20.793 --> 04:25.098
- All sales are final.
Danke schön, fräulein.

04:25.164 --> 04:26.633
- It's Saraline!

04:26.699 --> 04:30.003
- Can I interest you
in hand-carved replicas

04:30.069 --> 04:31.904
of famous animal
sidekicks,

04:31.971 --> 04:33.539
from TV and film,

04:33.606 --> 04:34.507
that I made?

04:34.574 --> 04:36.709
- Oh, I didn't
know you whittled.

04:36.776 --> 04:37.710
- Just a whittle.

04:37.777 --> 04:39.612
- We're not here to
sell, you fools.

04:39.679 --> 04:40.647
This is a cover.

04:40.713 --> 04:42.248
- Well, technically,
it's a duvet.

04:42.315 --> 04:43.549
- Wait.

04:43.616 --> 04:46.119
- [scanner beeps]
- Look.

04:46.185 --> 04:47.353
- The Pack Rat!

04:47.420 --> 04:49.989
- Not her.
What she's holding.

04:50.056 --> 04:52.058
Get ready, gentlemen,

04:52.125 --> 04:53.593
I think I've found
us a steal.

04:53.660 --> 04:55.294
- Looks like more
of an iron alloy.

04:55.361 --> 04:56.963
- [grunts]
- [gasps]

04:58.698 --> 05:01.134
- Sorry. Not for sale.
Neither is that. Nope.

05:01.200 --> 05:02.869
Not that. Hands off.
Not for sale.

05:02.935 --> 05:05.538
- Ansi, it's almost like you
don't wanna sell your stuff.

05:05.605 --> 05:08.074
- I already told you.
I don't wanna sell my stuff.

05:08.141 --> 05:09.842
- That's why it's
almost like that.

05:09.909 --> 05:11.044
- [playing music]

05:11.110 --> 05:12.111
- Hey! Lips off, lippy!

05:12.178 --> 05:13.846
There's no way
I'm selling that.

05:13.913 --> 05:15.381
- OLLY:
Why? What is it?

05:15.448 --> 05:16.949
- It's a toy calliope
that my mom gave me.

05:17.016 --> 05:19.419
My dad must've thrown it
into the box by accident.

05:19.485 --> 05:21.854
It's really special.
- So you just blow into it?

05:21.921 --> 05:23.656
- Olly!
- Blow into what?

05:23.723 --> 05:25.258
- Julia! What are
you doing here?

05:25.324 --> 05:26.659
- I'm running
the Hop &amp; Bop.

05:26.726 --> 05:28.327
But first I thought
I'd Swap and Shop.

05:28.394 --> 05:31.564
Ooh, I love these
vintage clothes.

05:31.631 --> 05:33.966
They're perfect for this
year's disco theme.

05:34.033 --> 05:35.134
- Take 'em all.

05:35.201 --> 05:37.136
They smell like loneliness
and vampire.

05:37.203 --> 05:39.272
- Vampire?
- Um, uh, yeah.

05:39.338 --> 05:41.441
Yeah, vampire.
Uh, it's a scent.

05:41.507 --> 05:43.376
- A scent? I'll take 'em.

05:43.443 --> 05:46.946
[gasps]
This is so adorable.

05:47.013 --> 05:47.980
Can I try it?

05:48.047 --> 05:49.482
- Lips off, lippy!
It's not for sale!

05:49.549 --> 05:50.883
- Oh, that's too bad.

05:50.950 --> 05:53.386
As soon as I saw it,
I fell in love with it.

05:53.453 --> 05:55.521
- I know how you feel.
- What?

05:55.588 --> 05:58.257
- I mean, uh, take it.
It's yours.

05:58.324 --> 06:01.327
- Lips on. For sale.
- Thanks.

06:01.394 --> 06:03.796
[muffled] You guys are
my weirdest friends.

06:03.863 --> 06:07.400
[playing music]

06:07.467 --> 06:09.202
- That wasn't so bad.

06:09.268 --> 06:11.771
I gave away a piece
of my childhood.

06:11.838 --> 06:12.705
It doesn't hurt.

06:12.772 --> 06:16.042
Ohhhh! Right in
the nostalgia!

06:16.109 --> 06:18.344
[gasps]
The Pack Rat!

06:18.411 --> 06:19.679
- Some Pack Rat.

06:19.746 --> 06:21.581
All I'm packing
is some piece of junk

06:21.647 --> 06:23.549
I was swindled
into buying.

06:23.616 --> 06:25.284
Do you like heavy metal?

06:25.351 --> 06:26.586
- Only when I'm studying.

06:26.652 --> 06:28.588
- Here. Maybe you'll
find a use for it.

06:28.654 --> 06:30.389
- [object thuds]
- [groans]

06:30.456 --> 06:32.759
[grunting]

06:32.825 --> 06:34.961
Julia! Hey, Julia!

06:35.027 --> 06:36.129
Care to make a swap?

06:36.195 --> 06:37.997
- I'm more into the shop
and the hop.

06:38.064 --> 06:40.199
And, of course, the bop.
Not so much the swap.

06:40.266 --> 06:42.168
- Well, check this
thing out.

06:42.235 --> 06:43.870
- [object thuds]
- What is it?

06:43.936 --> 06:45.605
- What isn't it?

06:45.671 --> 06:47.306
It's a back scratcher.
[grunting]

06:47.373 --> 06:49.008
A comb.
[groaning]

06:49.075 --> 06:50.409
- [object thuds]

06:50.476 --> 06:53.045
- A can opener.
[groaning]

06:53.112 --> 06:54.614
- [liquid splats]

06:54.680 --> 06:56.949
- Well, what do
you want for it?

06:57.016 --> 07:00.620
- I was thinking, uh,
how about my toy calliope?

07:00.686 --> 07:01.587
- Hmmm...

07:01.654 --> 07:05.024
Okay. But you owe me.
- Owe?

07:05.091 --> 07:06.592
- Owe.
- Oh, owe.

07:06.659 --> 07:08.094
That makes more sense.

07:08.161 --> 07:13.399
- ♪

07:13.466 --> 07:15.101
- I got it.

07:15.168 --> 07:17.069
Whew, I'm so glad
I have all my--

07:17.136 --> 07:18.204
[gasps]

07:18.271 --> 07:19.372
Where's my stuff?!

07:19.438 --> 07:20.706
- You should have
seen it, Ansi.

07:20.773 --> 07:22.375
Everything sold
like hotcakes--

07:22.441 --> 07:23.776
except for these hotcakes.

07:23.843 --> 07:25.745
- This is the last
of my stuff.

07:25.812 --> 07:27.446
- And I'm the last
of my kind.

07:27.513 --> 07:29.248
- And this is the last
of my third brunch.

07:29.315 --> 07:30.883
[chomping]

07:30.950 --> 07:33.119
- I can't believe you sold
my stuff without asking me.

07:33.186 --> 07:35.655
- But now you can get
all new stuff--like me.

07:35.721 --> 07:37.356
What do you think
I should collect, Ansi?

07:37.423 --> 07:38.591
- Don't ask me.

07:38.658 --> 07:40.459
It's gotta be something
that means a lot to you.

07:40.526 --> 07:42.028
- Something that means
a lot to me.

07:42.094 --> 07:43.029
Hmmm...

07:43.095 --> 07:46.399
Like many, mutts, myriads.

07:46.465 --> 07:49.168
- [dramatic music]

07:58.744 --> 08:00.713
- Well, look what
we have here.

08:00.780 --> 08:03.349
All dressed up
and nowhere to go.

08:03.416 --> 08:04.584
- All right, clothes,

08:04.650 --> 08:07.253
you have something
that belongs to us.

08:07.320 --> 08:08.821
{\an8}- BOTH:
[gasp]

08:08.888 --> 08:10.790
{\an8}- I think he's
pullin' our legs.

08:10.857 --> 08:12.525
[yelping]

08:12.592 --> 08:14.660
- Flowershirt
and Masterson?

08:14.727 --> 08:29.609
- ♪

08:29.675 --> 08:32.178
- [heavy punch]
- [gasps]

08:33.946 --> 08:37.350
- All right, Mothballs,
hand over the item.

08:37.416 --> 08:40.253
- Now, we can do
this the easy way or--

08:40.318 --> 08:43.456
Whoa! Easy way!
I choose easy!

08:43.522 --> 08:45.224
- [heavy thud]
- [groans]

08:45.291 --> 08:47.026
- I've gotta call
the others.

08:47.093 --> 08:49.195
- [sighs]

08:50.963 --> 08:53.566
- Hey, aren't you
the famous Pack Rat

08:53.633 --> 08:55.668
that recently spent
all your money

08:55.735 --> 08:59.238
on a useless
piece of junk?

08:59.305 --> 09:00.640
- Gimme another lemonade.

09:00.706 --> 09:02.375
This time,
charge me double.

09:02.441 --> 09:04.810
[slurping]
- MAN: [laughing]

09:04.877 --> 09:07.713
My, how the mighty
have fallen.

09:07.780 --> 09:10.750
If you ever want
an overpriced disco ball,

09:10.816 --> 09:13.085
you know who to ask for.

09:13.152 --> 09:16.355
Lenny's Overpriced
Disco Balls--table 7.

09:16.422 --> 09:18.624
- [sighing]

09:18.691 --> 09:20.493
- ANSI:
Saraline, I need you!

09:20.559 --> 09:22.461
- Nobody needs me, Ansi.

09:22.528 --> 09:24.263
I'm a Pack Rat
who can't bargain her way

09:24.330 --> 09:26.265
out of a wet paper bag.

09:26.332 --> 09:28.234
- ANSI: Stop mixing
metaphors and get over here!

09:28.301 --> 09:29.201
You have to see this.

09:29.268 --> 09:30.369
- Fine.

09:30.436 --> 09:32.204
Keep the change.

09:32.271 --> 09:34.440
- Hm, what to collect?

09:34.507 --> 09:35.908
- WOMAN: Taxidermy
prairie animals?

09:35.975 --> 09:37.243
- How much do
they gopher?

09:37.310 --> 09:39.211
- MAN: Butter pats from
international hotels?

09:39.278 --> 09:40.546
- Too rich for my blood.

09:40.613 --> 09:42.014
- WOMAN #2:
Comics in mint condition?

09:42.081 --> 09:44.650
- I'm not getting
any mint. Paper, maybe.

09:45.952 --> 09:47.787
Finding stuff
to collect is hard.

09:47.853 --> 09:50.256
It has to be something
I really care about.

09:50.323 --> 09:51.590
- [signal beeping]
- Ansi!

09:51.657 --> 09:52.992
- ANSI: Olly,
I need your help!

09:53.059 --> 09:54.794
- I'll be right
there, buddy.

09:54.860 --> 09:56.696
I guess my collection
will just have to--

09:56.762 --> 09:58.564
interrupting gasp!

09:58.631 --> 10:01.233
It's perfect!
I'll take it.

10:01.300 --> 10:04.370
- WOMAN #3: Great. I'll throw
in the flashlight, too.

10:04.437 --> 10:07.340
- [dramatic music]

10:07.406 --> 10:08.641
- This better be
good, Ansi.

10:08.708 --> 10:11.577
You interrupted a perfectly
pathetic pity party.

10:11.644 --> 10:14.080
- Look, Andrei's
clothes came to life!

10:14.146 --> 10:16.182
- Oh.
- And they learned Kung fu.

10:18.784 --> 10:20.019
- It looks like
they're fighting over--

10:20.086 --> 10:23.589
[gasps] The piece of junk
that old man sold me.

10:23.656 --> 10:25.758
- Hey, guys,
what'd I miss?

10:25.825 --> 10:27.393
- Olly, you're late.
Were you shopping?

10:27.460 --> 10:29.862
- I finally found something
I really care about to collect.

10:29.929 --> 10:32.264
- It's really selfish of you
to only think of yourself.

10:32.331 --> 10:34.633
- How else am I supposed
to only think of myself?

10:37.403 --> 10:40.439
- Saraline's right.
They're fighting over this.

10:40.506 --> 10:42.608
What is it?
- Uh-oh!

10:42.675 --> 10:44.043
- ALL:
[panting]

10:44.110 --> 10:46.312
- Come on! We'll lose
them in the crowd.

10:46.379 --> 10:49.081
- ALL:
[panting]

10:49.148 --> 10:51.384
- Funsy! Another
precious treasure.

10:51.450 --> 10:54.353
- Olly, it's not the time
to add to your collection.

10:54.420 --> 10:56.655
- ALL:
[panting]

10:56.722 --> 10:59.025
- [grunts]

10:59.091 --> 11:03.195
- ♪

11:03.262 --> 11:05.698
- Groovy. Crazy.

11:05.765 --> 11:07.433
- FLOWERSHIRT &amp; MASTERSON:
[panting]

11:09.402 --> 11:10.736
- I just don't get it.

11:10.803 --> 11:13.672
Why would anyone want this
worthless piece of junk?

11:13.739 --> 11:15.307
- Uh, I'm right here,
you know?

11:15.374 --> 11:16.809
- That's your brother.

11:16.876 --> 11:19.378
- ANDREI: Harpoon?
Apiary hood?

11:19.445 --> 11:22.348
Tap shoes? Anyone?

11:22.415 --> 11:23.716
Half off.

11:23.783 --> 11:25.217
Both halves off.

11:25.284 --> 11:27.119
All four quarters off.

11:27.186 --> 11:29.422
- Ansi, hurry up!

11:29.488 --> 11:30.856
- [grunting]
I'm trying.

11:30.923 --> 11:32.425
This thing is heavy.

11:35.294 --> 11:36.695
- Wait a second.

11:40.699 --> 11:42.068
Just as I suspected.

11:42.134 --> 11:44.603
The clothing
is ordinary polyester.

11:44.670 --> 11:46.739
But it's powered by beam.

11:46.806 --> 11:48.007
- That rainbow gas?

11:48.074 --> 11:49.975
- It's using the clothes
as a host body.

11:50.042 --> 11:51.677
But if we destroy
the clothing,

11:51.744 --> 11:53.512
the gas should dissipate.

11:53.579 --> 11:55.147
- Watch for leaks.
I like it.

11:55.214 --> 11:56.649
[screams]

11:56.715 --> 11:59.452
- It's all ours.

11:59.518 --> 12:02.021
- Fire.
- It's way hot.

12:04.290 --> 12:05.891
- Here, take this.
- No, you take it.

12:05.958 --> 12:07.293
- I don't want it.

12:07.359 --> 12:09.128
- Well, what makes
you think I want it?

12:09.195 --> 12:10.830
- We'll take it.

12:13.199 --> 12:15.434
- Hey, Ansi.
I was looking for you.

12:15.501 --> 12:17.670
- You were?
Little old me?

12:17.736 --> 12:19.305
Little young me?

12:19.371 --> 12:22.374
- Yeah, I'm rounding up people
for the Hop &amp; Bop.

12:22.441 --> 12:23.509
- [sighing]

12:23.576 --> 12:24.977
[screams]

12:25.044 --> 12:26.745
- You're coming, right?

12:26.812 --> 12:28.180
- [screams]

12:28.247 --> 12:30.149
Coming to what now?
- The Hop &amp; Bop.

12:30.216 --> 12:32.551
Why are you spinning
me around?

12:32.618 --> 12:33.986
- It's, uh,
one of my moves.

12:34.053 --> 12:37.690
- Oh, wow. Save it for
the dance floor.

12:37.756 --> 12:40.693
Don't forget--
you owe me.

12:40.759 --> 12:42.027
- [sighs]

12:42.094 --> 12:43.295
[screams]

12:43.362 --> 12:45.698
Come on, Olly, let's--

12:45.764 --> 12:46.799
Olly?

12:46.866 --> 12:48.701
- A collector's work
is never done.

12:48.767 --> 12:50.136
- You know, we could
use your help.

12:50.202 --> 12:52.805
- And I could use your sink
after I use your bathroom,

12:52.872 --> 12:54.373
but I usually don't.

12:54.440 --> 12:59.445
- ♪

12:59.512 --> 13:01.247
- You can have it, here.

13:01.313 --> 13:04.483
- ♪

13:04.550 --> 13:05.918
- Quick, under the table.

13:05.985 --> 13:07.086
- ANSI:
Great idea, Olly.

13:07.153 --> 13:08.354
This is the perfect
hiding spot.

13:08.420 --> 13:10.689
- I was just looking for
a place to put my gum.

13:10.756 --> 13:12.091
- [gum splats]
- What are we hiding from?

13:12.158 --> 13:13.692
- FLOWERSHIRT:
Those kids are gone.

13:13.759 --> 13:14.994
- MASTERSON:
Maybe they went this way.

13:15.060 --> 13:17.696
- [running footsteps]

13:17.763 --> 13:22.134
- ♪

13:22.201 --> 13:26.105
- Hm, the synthetic fibers
are ultra-sensitive to heat.

13:26.172 --> 13:28.541
- All right, so let me
get this straight.

13:28.607 --> 13:30.242
That thing is after
this thing,

13:30.309 --> 13:32.678
so, this thing
must be something.

13:32.745 --> 13:34.547
- Good. It helps
to get specific.

13:34.613 --> 13:35.714
- Whatever it is,

13:35.781 --> 13:37.283
if we don't destroy
those clothes,

13:37.349 --> 13:39.185
they're going to keep coming
back until they get it.

13:39.251 --> 13:42.354
So, let's regroup with Andrei
and come up with a plan.

13:47.226 --> 13:49.828
- Ansi, I can't wait to
show you my collection.

13:49.895 --> 13:51.864
I've been working on it
for a whole nine minutes.

13:51.931 --> 13:53.232
- Your collection?

13:53.299 --> 13:54.967
Olly, why do you
think I'd want to

13:55.034 --> 13:56.769
see your collection
right now?

13:56.835 --> 13:58.671
- Because we share
a lot of the same tastes--

13:58.737 --> 14:01.473
like a hundred percent.

14:01.540 --> 14:03.042
See?

14:03.108 --> 14:06.912
- My first 50-foot
USB cord?

14:06.979 --> 14:08.981
My kaleidoscope?

14:09.048 --> 14:12.117
My third 50-foot
USB cord?

14:12.184 --> 14:14.320
Olly, you bought back
all my old stuff!

14:14.386 --> 14:16.288
- I knew how much
it meant to you--

14:16.355 --> 14:18.424
which is why it meant
a lot to me.

14:18.490 --> 14:19.858
- Thanks, Olly.

14:19.925 --> 14:21.393
I'm never letting go
of this stuff again.

14:21.460 --> 14:23.662
- Ansi, I need you to
let go of all this stuff.

14:23.729 --> 14:24.964
- What?

14:25.030 --> 14:27.266
- I can use it to stop
those clothes.

14:27.333 --> 14:30.202
- But this isn't just stuff.
It's...like...memories...

14:30.269 --> 14:32.371
of all the places
I've ever lived...

14:32.438 --> 14:34.773
and all the printers
I've hooked up there.

14:34.840 --> 14:35.841
- But you live here now.

14:35.908 --> 14:37.710
- And we have Wi-Fi.

14:37.776 --> 14:39.178
- Yeah, don't you see?

14:39.245 --> 14:41.113
You've gotta get rid of
that stuff and move on.

14:41.180 --> 14:42.848
That's the point
she's trying to make.

14:42.915 --> 14:44.350
- No, it's not.
- Oh.

14:44.416 --> 14:46.585
- Ansi, you don't have
to hang on to the past

14:46.652 --> 14:48.254
or throw it away.

14:48.320 --> 14:49.922
You have to give
the past to me

14:49.989 --> 14:51.624
so I can create
a double refractive

14:51.690 --> 14:52.825
emulating heat
ray to incinerate

14:52.891 --> 14:54.760
a living leisure
suit from the '70s.

14:54.827 --> 14:55.961
- You stole that
from Lincoln.

14:56.028 --> 14:58.664
- Fine. [sighs]
It's all yours.

14:58.731 --> 15:00.699
Goodbye, USB Arthur.

15:00.766 --> 15:02.234
Thank you for
being a friend.

15:02.301 --> 15:03.969
- You won't
regret it, Ansi.

15:04.036 --> 15:06.138
- Oh, 4:00 o'clock!

15:06.205 --> 15:07.906
Oh, and there's the suit.

15:07.973 --> 15:09.141
- You two lead
that retro reject

15:09.208 --> 15:11.043
to an open area
with no one around.

15:11.110 --> 15:13.012
Andrei,
you stay with me.

15:13.078 --> 15:14.880
We've got a heat
ray to build.

15:14.947 --> 15:16.048
- Hey, John Ravolta!

15:16.115 --> 15:17.916
Yeah, I'm talkin' to you,
Funk Yard Dog.

15:17.983 --> 15:19.685
This way!

15:19.752 --> 15:32.865
- ♪

15:32.931 --> 15:35.301
- Have I mentioned how
heavy this thing is?

15:35.367 --> 15:36.702
- I'll take it
from here, buddy.

15:36.769 --> 15:38.470
Hmph!
- Thanks.

15:38.537 --> 15:39.772
Thanks a lot.

15:39.838 --> 15:41.707
Is he still out there?

15:41.774 --> 15:43.108
- He's so dumb.

15:43.175 --> 15:44.977
{\an8}We're right behind him
and he doesn't even see us.

15:45.044 --> 15:46.912
- Yeah, it makes you
feel really smart.

15:46.979 --> 15:48.047
- It sure does.

15:48.113 --> 15:49.848
- BOTH:
[sighing]

15:49.915 --> 15:51.650
[screaming]

15:53.385 --> 15:55.487
- BOTH:
[frightened gasps]

15:55.554 --> 15:57.690
- Now there are
three more of those guys.

15:57.756 --> 16:02.761
- ♪

16:02.828 --> 16:05.464
- They're getting away.
How are we gonna stop them?

16:05.531 --> 16:06.632
- Olly. Ansi.

16:06.699 --> 16:09.635
You're just in time
for my sound check.

16:09.702 --> 16:11.937
- [disco music playing]

16:12.004 --> 16:17.710
♪

16:17.776 --> 16:20.346
- Music. They can dance.

16:20.412 --> 16:22.281
- OLLY: Of course.
It all makes sense.

16:22.348 --> 16:23.349
I noticed that clothing

16:23.415 --> 16:25.317
completes the sounds
of the '70s.

16:25.384 --> 16:26.885
- ANSI:
That doesn't make sense.

16:26.952 --> 16:28.520
- Anyone ever tell
you you build

16:28.587 --> 16:30.522
anti-clothing artillery
really quickly?

16:30.589 --> 16:32.524
- It just needs
one final piece--

16:32.591 --> 16:34.293
a multi-faceted
reflective sphere

16:34.360 --> 16:37.029
that orbits
at about 10 rpm.

16:37.096 --> 16:38.097
- You mean a disco ball?

16:38.163 --> 16:39.498
That guy's got
a bunch of 'em.

16:39.565 --> 16:40.999
- Why did I pay
three times more

16:41.066 --> 16:43.168
for this disco ball
than I should have?

16:43.235 --> 16:44.803
- Well, that's what
happens when you come to

16:44.870 --> 16:47.106
Lenny's Overpriced
Disco Balls,

16:47.172 --> 16:50.042
now with three
inconvenient locations,

16:50.109 --> 16:52.144
all in Piranha.

16:52.211 --> 16:55.614
- Forget it. Nobody
could close that deal.

16:55.681 --> 16:56.982
- Nobody but...

16:57.049 --> 16:59.251
The Pack Mouse.
- It's Pack Rat.

16:59.318 --> 17:00.853
- Sorry, I only heard
you say it, like, once.

17:00.919 --> 17:03.789
- It doesn't matter.
That's all in the past now.

17:03.856 --> 17:05.758
- Well, somebody told me
you have to take the past

17:05.824 --> 17:08.426
and turn it into a laser...
or something.

17:08.493 --> 17:10.796
And since we've already had,
like, three pep talks,

17:10.863 --> 17:12.631
just go do that.

17:14.967 --> 17:16.234
- Hmph!

17:16.300 --> 17:19.538
- Well, look who it is--
the Pack Rat.

17:19.605 --> 17:21.440
You don't know
when to quit, do you?

17:21.507 --> 17:23.675
- I'll take your biggest
disco ball, Lenny.

17:23.742 --> 17:26.278
- How are you going to
pay for it, Pack Rat?

17:26.345 --> 17:30.115
You're already out of cheese.
[laughing]

17:30.182 --> 17:33.118
- Watch and learn.

17:33.185 --> 17:36.021
- ♪ Ooh ooh ooh ooh ♪

17:36.088 --> 17:36.989
♪ Pack Rat ♪

17:37.055 --> 17:39.291
♪ She's the Pack Rat ♪

17:39.358 --> 17:40.859
♪ She's the Pack,
Pack, Pack ♪

17:40.926 --> 17:42.294
♪ She's the Pack Rat ♪

17:42.361 --> 17:43.729
- WOMEN &amp; KIDS:
[gasping]

17:43.796 --> 17:44.897
- ♪ The Pack Rat ♪

17:44.963 --> 17:46.198
♪ She's the Pack Rat ♪♪

17:46.265 --> 17:50.002
- Oh, I got pack ratted
by the original Pack Rat.

17:50.068 --> 17:52.004
But this ain't over yet.

17:52.070 --> 17:54.606
Oh, I guess it is over.

17:54.673 --> 17:56.341
- ANSI: Okay, while
they're distracted,

17:56.408 --> 17:57.976
let's get that piece
of metal back.

17:58.043 --> 17:59.077
- Why?

17:59.144 --> 18:00.546
- Because it's
seemingly important.

18:00.612 --> 18:02.181
- It is seemingly
important, isn't it?

18:02.247 --> 18:03.282
- Let's go.

18:03.348 --> 18:05.517
- [disco music continues]

18:05.584 --> 18:06.819
- [screams]

18:06.885 --> 18:14.326
- ♪

18:14.393 --> 18:15.961
- Mind if I...
cut in?

18:16.028 --> 18:17.029
- Oh!

18:17.095 --> 18:18.230
- Thanks, Ansi.

18:18.297 --> 18:21.366
I was so not into him.

18:21.433 --> 18:23.869
- Time to get
this party started.

18:23.936 --> 18:25.137
- Yeah, right.

18:25.204 --> 18:26.472
We could do that thing
we've been practicing.

18:26.538 --> 18:28.240
- Just don't drop
me this time.

18:28.307 --> 18:31.043
- I'll be gentle
as a lady.

18:31.109 --> 18:33.879
- [disco music continues]

18:33.946 --> 18:35.781
- ANSI:
[grunting]

18:35.848 --> 18:36.982
- OLLY:
Ah!

18:37.049 --> 18:38.917
- What's taking
Saraline so long?

18:38.984 --> 18:42.321
- [disco music continues]

18:42.387 --> 18:44.022
- I'm not even gonna ask.

18:44.089 --> 18:46.558
Andrei, help me
set this thing up.

18:46.625 --> 18:49.394
- Whoa! Whoa!
My feet! My feet!

18:49.461 --> 18:51.029
I'm moving my hips.

18:51.096 --> 18:53.165
My hips! Oh! Oh!

18:53.232 --> 18:54.800
- What is it?
Are you krumping?

18:54.867 --> 18:57.302
- I don't know.
I can't control it.

18:57.369 --> 18:58.937
Why is there always
something I can't control?

18:59.004 --> 19:01.607
- That's the double-edged
sword that is free will.

19:01.673 --> 19:06.178
Now angle me into position
for maximum funkification.

19:06.245 --> 19:08.313
[screams]

19:10.549 --> 19:11.984
- I always knew
it would end like this--

19:12.050 --> 19:14.686
beaten to a pulp by vicious
clothing in a flea market dance.

19:14.753 --> 19:16.355
- I always thought
I'd be 90 years old

19:16.421 --> 19:17.823
and surrounded
by loved ones.

19:17.890 --> 19:19.591
- Well, at least you
got the surrounded part.

19:19.658 --> 19:21.727
- ANSI: [gasps]
- [laser zaps]

19:26.732 --> 19:29.501
- Time for some
disco inferno.

19:29.568 --> 19:32.538
- [lasers blasting]

19:35.107 --> 19:36.942
- Ahhh! Oh!

19:37.009 --> 19:38.176
- Oh, hey, Ansi.

19:38.243 --> 19:40.178
Guess everyone's having
fun out there.

19:40.245 --> 19:42.948
- Yeah. Ha. Ha.
Turned on to--what?

19:43.015 --> 19:44.082
- What?

19:44.149 --> 19:46.752
- [lasers blasting]

19:51.456 --> 19:54.493
- It's working!
The beam is dispersing.

19:54.560 --> 19:57.696
- [lasers blasting]

19:57.763 --> 19:58.964
- [screaming]

19:59.031 --> 20:00.165
- [disc ball shatters]

20:00.232 --> 20:02.501
- [laser blasting]

20:02.568 --> 20:07.005
- JULIA: Okay, lovebirds,
time to slow things down.

20:07.072 --> 20:10.375
- [slower tempo disco]

20:12.311 --> 20:13.845
- Huh?

20:15.981 --> 20:18.317
- My liege.
- Who? Me?

20:18.383 --> 20:20.085
You've got
the wrong liege.

20:20.152 --> 20:21.153
No liege here.

20:21.219 --> 20:23.388
- Take the key.

20:24.923 --> 20:25.991
- ANDREI:
The key?

20:26.058 --> 20:27.492
Wait a minute.
Who are you?

20:27.559 --> 20:29.828
Are you a vampire?

20:29.895 --> 20:33.031
- Set us free.

20:33.098 --> 20:34.366
- Free from where?

20:34.433 --> 20:36.201
- From--
- Olly, now!

20:36.268 --> 20:39.104
- [unintelligible]
- [explosion]

20:39.171 --> 20:41.273
- No-o-o-o!

20:41.340 --> 20:42.608
Why did you do that?

20:42.674 --> 20:44.209
He was just about
to tell me.

20:44.276 --> 20:45.911
- We were trying
to save you.

20:45.978 --> 20:47.679
- Well, that's just...

20:47.746 --> 20:48.847
you're...

20:48.914 --> 20:50.582
chicken butt!

20:50.649 --> 20:53.385
I'll never meet another
vampire again!

20:53.452 --> 20:55.354
- Andrei, wait!
There's an app for that.

20:55.420 --> 20:56.722
- Hmmm...

20:56.788 --> 21:00.759
- If that thing's a key,
what does it unlock?

21:00.826 --> 21:04.096
I've gotta find that old
man who sold it to me.

21:04.162 --> 21:05.564
- I came for the Hop &amp; Bop.

21:05.631 --> 21:09.067
But it looks like
the Hop &amp; Bop had to stop.

21:09.134 --> 21:10.736
- Uh, well, yeah.

21:10.802 --> 21:13.538
- Oh, but what is
this you're holding here?

21:13.605 --> 21:17.009
I think this is a 1928
tin press calliope

21:17.075 --> 21:19.378
by Steinhausen Novelties.

21:19.444 --> 21:23.215
But I imagine such
a treasure is not for sale.

21:23.281 --> 21:24.950
- No, it's not for sale.

21:25.017 --> 21:27.219
But...you can have it.

21:27.285 --> 21:29.087
- I'll find a good
home for it.

21:29.154 --> 21:30.255
Every buyer has an item

21:30.322 --> 21:33.091
that fits them like
a key into a lock.

21:33.158 --> 21:34.926
Auf wiedersehen...

21:34.993 --> 21:36.428
Herr Molina.

21:37.295 --> 21:39.398
- JULIA: Whoa,
what happened here?

21:39.464 --> 21:41.667
It looks like somebody
really dropped the ball.

21:41.733 --> 21:43.235
- Let me help you
clean it up.

21:43.301 --> 21:44.436
- Thanks.

21:44.503 --> 21:46.204
But, first, I think
you owe me.

21:46.271 --> 21:49.307
- Slow? Oh? Owe.

21:49.374 --> 21:51.576
- [disco music playing]
- Ohhhh...

21:54.212 --> 21:57.649
- ♪

21:57.716 --> 21:59.718
- Watch your step.
- [heavy thud]

22:01.453 --> 22:17.669
- ♪
